Global Fungal Protein Market Insights
Fungal Protein Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 3.4 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 15.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Fungal Protein Market Overview
The global fungal protein market is witnessing significant growth, driven by the increasing demand for sustainable protein sources. In 2024, the market is valued at approximately USD 1.8 billion and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 7.5% during the forecast period from 2025 to 2030. This growth is attributed to the rising trend of plant-based protein alternatives and the growing popularity of fungi-based protein products across various sectors, including food and beverages, animal feed, and pharmaceuticals. As concerns over the environmental impact of traditional animal farming grow, fungal protein emerges as a viable, eco-friendly alternative to conventional proteins.

